<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:If a response is constructed without a content-reader callback (response->crc == NULL) but also without contiguous response->data covering the current rsp_write_position (for example when using MHD_create_response_from_iovec that results in data_iov being used rather than response->data), execution can reach the branch labelled "There is no way to reach this code". In other words, the comment is incorrect and that branch is potentially reachable (it handles the case when no callback is available to provide chunked data). Because there exists a feasible control-path to that block, the function contains code that was presumed unreachable and therefore the project violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1.
</scenario>
